nl.quintor.solitaire.models.state

Class GameState

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.quintor.solitaire.models.state.GameState

  • public final class GameState
extends java.lang.Object
    Class that holds the complete state of the game, consisting of 1 stock, 7 columns and 4 stacks of Decks, and two booleans gameOver and gameLost which together indicate if the game is over.

    It can also hold a waste deck, a list of moves, the number of times the stock has been cycled, the base score, the bonus time score and the start time of the game. These additional state variables can be used if additional features beyond the base game are implemented.

    Almost all methods are basic getters and setters, except for remember(RevertibleMove), forget(RevertibleMove), isGameOver() and getScore().
